\chapter{Authentication}

Authentication concerns ensuring that a claimed property indeed holds.
\Eg in user authentication, the verifier wants to ensure that the user indeed 
corresponds to the claimed identity.
There are, however, a variety of properties that we might be interested in 
verifying.

We need some basic terminology, which happens to be acronyms:
\ac{eID}, \DescribeAcro{eID};
\ac{CA}, \DescribeAcro{CA};
and more generally \iac{PKI}, \DescribeAcro{PKI}.
They are defined as follows.
